---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
        <head>
                <BaseHead title={`Start Here | ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="Jack Maguire writes about performance marketing, NYC food, AI tools, and philosophy. Start here for an introduction to his work and how to navigate the site." />
                <style>
                        .start-lede {
                                margin-bottom: 2rem;
                                padding-bottom: 1.3rem;
                                border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(85, 107, 47, 0.22);
                        }
                        .kicker {
                                margin: 0 0 0.45rem;
                                font-family: var(--font-outfit), sans-serif;
                                font-size: 0.72rem;
                                font-weight: 700;
                                color: var(--accent-dark);
                                text-transform: uppercase;
                                letter-spacing: 0.05em;
                        }
                        .start-lede p:last-child {
                                margin: 0;
                                color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
                                font-size: 1.05em;
                        }
                        .prose h2 {
                                font-size: 1.35em;
                                margin-top: 2em;
                                margin-bottom: 0.5em;
                                color: rgb(var(--black));
                        }
                        .prose p {
                                margin-bottom: 1.5em;
                                line-height: 1.8;
                                color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
                        }
                        .prose strong {
                                color: rgb(var(--black));
                        }
                        .note {
                                padding: 1.5em;
                                background-color: rgba(var(--gray-light), 0.2);
                                border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
                                margin: 2em 0;
                                font-style: italic;
                        }
                </style>
        </head>
        <body>
                <Header />
                <main>
                        <section class="start-lede">
                                <p class="kicker">Site orientation</p>
                                <h1>Start Here</h1>
                                <p>Start with the recurring threads: paid social systems, East Village life, food as fieldwork, travel by constraint, and presence as a practical discipline.</p>
                        </section>
                        <div class="prose">
				<p>I am Jack Maguire, a performance marketer and writer based in the East Village of New York City. This site collects essays, route plans, rankings, and firsthand evaluations across paid social media, urbanism, long-distance travel, restaurants, books, and AI tools.</p>

				<h2>Performance Marketing</h2>

				<p>My work as a Senior Paid Social Media Director focuses on scaling campaign structures across Meta, TikTok, and Snapchat. The advertising industry rewards noise, so I care about measurement, incrementality, creative testing, and the operational details that reveal where growth actually comes from.</p>

				<h2>Urbanism and the East Village</h2>

				<p>Living in the East Village gives the site a practical geography. Restaurants, coffee shops, sidewalk routines, transit friction, and small neighborhood economies all become observable systems. I write about cities through what I can actually walk, eat, notice, and test.</p>

				<h2>Long-Distance Travel</h2>

				<p>Travel functions as logistics under pressure. I care about train stations, border crossings, lodging friction, walking distance, and the point where a route becomes elegant rather than merely efficient. Thru-hiking the Appalachian Trail in ninety-nine days still shapes how I think about endurance, constraints, and attention.</p>

				<h2>Gastronomy</h2>

				<p>Food gives the site its most concrete research subject. I care about the chemistry of cooking, the logistics of restaurant operations, and the difference between a place with real point of view and a place with merely competent execution.</p>

				<h2>Philosophy of Presence</h2>

				<p>My intellectual interests focus on existentialism, phenomenology, and the limits of optimization. Meaning accumulates through ordinary experience: a quiet conversation, a shared meal, a demanding text, a walk that changes the day. The site keeps that tension visible.</p>

				<h2>Social Connection</h2>

				<p>Hosting, connecting, and bringing people together form the core of my social life. I value friendships built on shared vulnerability, intellectual honesty, and mutual respect, because a life organized only around output becomes too thin.</p>

				<h2>Synthesis</h2>

				<p>The essays on this site aim to clarify complex topics through direct prose. The method stays consistent: inspect incentives, compare real examples, notice physical constraints, and prefer firsthand evidence when possible.</p>
                        </div>
                </main>
                <Footer />
        </body>
</html>
